 However, Watts understanding of heat was far different from that of his successors
 Just as the laboratory chemist spent much time labouring over the furnace, so great ‘bottle kilns, named after their shape, loomed large in the working lives of potters
 But other products, including the creamware, were referred to only as ‘biscuitware after its first firing because of the colour, poros ity and absorbent qualities attained
